"What is the skeletal system?","The framework of bones supporting the body"
"What are the functions of the skeleton?","Support, protection, movement, blood cell production"
"What is a long bone?","A bone longer than it is wide e.g. femur"
"What is a short bone?","Small, cube-shaped bone e.g. carpals"
"What is a flat bone?","Thin bone e.g. ribs"
"What is an irregular bone?","Bone with complex shape e.g. vertebrae"
"What is the axial skeleton?","Central bones including skull and spine"
"What is the appendicular skeleton?","Limbs and girdles"
"What is a joint?","Where two bones meet"
"What is a hinge joint?","Allows flexion and extension e.g. elbow"
"What is a ball and socket joint?","Allows movement in all directions e.g. hip"
"What is a pivot joint?","Allows rotation e.g. neck"
"What is a condyloid joint?","Allows movement in two planes"
"What is a saddle joint?","Allows movement in two directions"
"What is flexion?","Decreasing angle at a joint"
"What is extension?","Increasing angle at a joint"
"What is abduction?","Movement away from midline"
"What is adduction?","Movement towards midline"
"What is rotation?","Circular movement around axis"
"What is circumduction?","Combination of movements forming a circle"
"What is the muscular system?","System of muscles enabling movement"
"What are antagonistic muscles?","Muscles working in pairs"
"What is an agonist?","Muscle causing movement"
"What is an antagonist?","Muscle opposing movement"
"What is a fixator?","Stabilises joint"
"What is a synergist?","Assists movement"
"What is a muscle fibre?","Single muscle cell"
"What is contraction?","Muscle shortening"
"What is relaxation?","Muscle lengthening"
"What is isotonic contraction?","Muscle changes length"
"What is isometric contraction?","Muscle stays same length"
"What is concentric contraction?","Muscle shortens"
"What is eccentric contraction?","Muscle lengthens under tension"
"What is cardiac muscle?","Muscle of the heart"
"What is skeletal muscle?","Voluntary muscle"
"What is smooth muscle?","Involuntary muscle"
"What is the cardiovascular system?","Heart and blood vessels"
"What is heart rate?","Beats per minute"
"What is stroke volume?","Blood pumped per beat"
"What is cardiac output?","HR x SV"
"What is the respiratory system?","Breathing system"
"What is tidal volume?","Air per breath"
"What is vital capacity?","Max air exhaled"
"What is oxygen uptake?","Oxygen used by body"
"What is haemoglobin?","Protein carrying oxygen"
"What is diffusion?","Movement from high to low concentration"
"What is aerobic respiration?","Energy with oxygen"
"What is anaerobic respiration?","Energy without oxygen"
"What is ATP?","Energy currency of body"

"What is ATP-PC system?","Immediate energy system"
"What is glycolytic system?","Short-term energy system"
"What is aerobic system?","Long-term energy system"
"What is lactic acid?","By-product of anaerobic exercise"
"What is oxygen debt?","Extra oxygen needed after exercise"
"What is EPOC?","Excess post-exercise oxygen consumption"
"What is VO2 max?","Max oxygen uptake"
"What is recovery?","Return to resting state"
"What is muscle fatigue?","Reduced ability to contract"
"What is fast twitch fibres?","Explosive fibres"
"What is slow twitch fibres?","Endurance fibres"
"What is motor unit?","Nerve + muscle fibres"
"What is neuromuscular junction?","Connection nerve-muscle"
"What is sliding filament theory?","Muscle contraction mechanism"
"What is actin?","Thin filament"
"What is myosin?","Thick filament"
"What is sarcomere?","Contractile unit"
"What is tendon?","Connects muscle to bone"
"What is ligament?","Connects bone to bone"
"What is cartilage?","Reduces friction"
"What is synovial fluid?","Lubricates joint"
"What is plane of movement?","Direction of movement"
"What is sagittal plane?","Divides left/right"
"What is frontal plane?","Divides front/back"
"What is transverse plane?","Divides top/bottom"
"What is axis?","Line of rotation"
"What is transverse axis?","Horizontal axis"
"What is longitudinal axis?","Vertical axis"
"What is frontal axis?","Side-to-side axis"

